{{BLP sources|date=October 2016}} {{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]] --> | name = T.K. Damodaran |image = T.K.D. muzhappilangad.jpg | pseudonym = T.K.D. Muzhappilangad | occupation = Author | nationality = Indian | genre = [[Novel]]s, [[screenplay]], [[children's literature]] | subject = | living=yes | movement = | awards = [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Award for Children's Literature]] }}
'''T.K Damodaran''' (born 1946), popularly known as '''T.K.D. Muzhappilangad''', is an Indian author, [[screenplay writer]], critic and orator. He is an acclaimed children's story writer in [[Malayalam]], who has won several awards including [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/ksa/Awards/Endowments/Award_Balasahityam.htm |title=Sri Padmanabha Swamy Endowment Award for Literature for Children |website=Keralasahityaakademi.org |date= |accessdate=2016-10-27}}</ref> His book ''Unnikkuttanum kadhakaliyum'' received the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Award for Children's Literature]] in 1983.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://secure.mathrubhumi.com/books/author/533/muzhappilangaadu-t.k.d |title=Mathrubhumi &#124;&#124; books |website=Secure.mathrubhumi.com |date= |accessdate=2016-10-27}}</ref> He was born in [[Muzhappilangad]], a coastal village in [[Kerala]]. Besides children's literature he wrote four novels, sixteen essays on various subjects, five biographies and five plays.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://122.165.117.71/cgi-bin/koha/opac-search.pl?q=ccl=au%3A%22Muzhappilangad.%20T.%20K.%20D.%22&sort_by=relevance_dsc&limit=au:Muzhappilangad.%20T.%20K.%20D |title=Ernakulam Public Library catalog › Results of search for 'au:"Muzhappilangad. T. K. D." and au:Muzhappilangad. T. K. D' |website=122.165.117.71 |date= |accessdate=2016-10-27}}</ref>
